Around  p.m PERIOD Friday afternoon the power went out across the University of Oregons campus PERIOD The power for stoplights around town was reported to be out as well as at major apartment complexes around the campus area including thirteenth and Olive and  Franklin PERIOD

A spokesperson for Eugene Water and Electric Board said they were unsure about what caused the outage PERIOD Immediately after the incident EWEB dispatched teams to look for possible causes like a downed wire or fallen trees or branches PERIOD

The power was restored to most locations within minutes of the outages PERIOD

This post will be updated as more information becomes available PERIOD
